    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Arctium lappa are antioxidant and anti-inflammatory, which contribute to its potential in reducing oxidative stress and inflammation, thereby offering hepatoprotective effects by shielding liver cells from damage and promoting their regeneration. The bioactive compounds responsible for these properties include flavonoids, which are known to scavenge free radicals and saponins that exhibit anti-inflammatory activity. Additionally, the antimicrobial properties of Arctium lappa are attributed to the presence of volatile oils, which have been shown to inhibit the growth of various microorganisms, including bacteria and fungi, thus preventing infections. Furthermore, the cardioprotective effects of this plant are thought to be mediated by its ability to reduce lipid peroxidation and improve blood lipid profiles, thereby lowering the risk of cardiovascular disease. The unique combination of these bioactive compounds makes Arctium lappa a valuable resource for the development of novel therapeutic agents.",
