    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Arctium lappa are arctiin, a coumarin responsible for its antispasmodic and anti-inflammatory properties, inulin, a type of fructan that acts as a prebiotic and soothes digestive issues, arctigenin, a lignan that exhibits antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, saponins, which have been shown to have immunomodulatory and antiviral effects, and arctiopicrin, a sesquiterpene lactone that has been found to have anti-inflammatory and analgesic properties. Arctium lappa's high arctiin content is responsible for its ability to relax smooth muscles and reduce inflammation. Arctigenin has been shown to have a synergistic effect with other lignans, enhancing their antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities. Saponins in Arctium lappa stimulate the immune system and inhibit viral replication, while arctiopicrin's anti-inflammatory effects are thought to be mediated by its ability to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes. The combination of these constituents in Arctium lappa contributes to its traditional use in treating various health conditions, including digestive issues, inflammation, and viral infections.",
