    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Arctium lappa are tincture, tea, infusion, salve, and decoction. A tincture of Arctium lappa is made by soaking the plant's roots in a solvent such as ethanol or glycerin, which is used to treat digestive issues and skin problems. Arctium lappa tea is prepared by steeping the plant's roots in hot water, and is used to support liver and kidney function. The roots of Arctium lappa can be made into an infusion by steeping them in cold water, which is used to treat fever and inflammation. A salve is prepared by mixing the plant's roots with a carrier oil, such as coconut or olive oil, to treat skin conditions like eczema and acne, while a decoction is made by boiling the roots in water to treat digestive issues and skin problems.",
