    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Arctium lappa improperly include developing an allergic reaction, which can occur in individuals who are sensitive to the plant's constituents, such as inulin or taraxasterol. Experiencing allergic reactions to Arctium lappa can range from mild symptoms like hives or itching to severe reactions like anaphylaxis. Interacting with medications is another potential side effect, as Arctium lappa may enhance the effects of blood thinners or decrease the effectiveness of certain medications, such as diabetes medications, due to its inulin content. Ingesting large quantities of Arctium lappa may also induce diarrhea, a condition that can lead to dehydration and electrolyte imbalances. Furthermore, consuming excessive amounts of Arctium lappa may cause kidney damage due to its high levels of inulin, which can increase kidney workload and potentially damage kidney tissues over time."
